node.text:
Pool party brownies☀️🌺:
Having a pool party today & brownies are a must!

•Brownie mix
•1 egg 
•1/3 cup oil
•1/3 cup water
•Oreos
•Hersey syrup 
•Cookie dough

Start by washing yo hands!👏🏼🧼Make brownie mix, then in a baking dish, flatten out cookie dough in bottom of dish, pour half brownie mix in over dough, & then set in Oreos to cover surface, then drizzle syrup over Oreos. Top with remaining brownie mix & bake at 350° for 35 min! 🤎🍫🤎

node.text:
Manicotti🍝:

(Prep time: 20 minutes // Cook time: 25 minutes)

•manicotti shells
•ricotta (I usually use the larger container)
•cream cheese (whole block)
•Italian sausage (1lb)
•yellow onion🧅
•finely grated parm cheese🧀
•cento crushed tomatoes (28oz can)
•fresh parsley
•minced garlic 
•fennel seed 
•granulated sugar 
•garlic powder 
•onion powder 
•dried basil

•Meet: in a pan, brown half a yellow onion & ground Italian sausage. Mix in a tablespoon of minced garlic and make sure meat is finely ground. Once cooked, let it cool to room temperature. 

•Filling: In a large bowl combine, ricotta, softened cream cheese, 1/2 cup of grated parm, 1/3 cup of chopped parsley, 1 table spoon of minced garlic, salt & pepper, & meat and onion mixture (including grease) that has been cooling. 

•Sauce: in the same pan that you cooked the meat, pour in can of crushed tomatoes, 1/2 cup of water, 1 tablespoon of granulated sugar, 1 tablespoon of dried basil, 1/2 a tablespoon of fennel seed, salt & pepper, sprinkle in some garlic and onion powder and fresh parsley. Let simmer while you stuff shells. 

•Stuff shells (I usually pour filling into a gallon size zip lock back, snip the corner with scissors and stuff the shells that way- but I was out of bags.🤪) with filling all the way through and lay in a greased baking dish. Once all the shells are in, top with sauce and bake (covered) at 425 for 25 minutes. *Bonus: if you love cheese…. Top with mozzarella cheese after adding sauce!❤️🤍
